disregard /ˌdɪsrɪˈɡɑːd/

(disregarding,disregarded,disregards) 

1. V-T If you disregard something, you ignore it or do not take account of it. 对…置之不理 

例： He disregarded the advice of his executives. 他对主管们的建议置之不理。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Disregard is also a noun. 忽视 

例： Whoever planted the bomb showed a total disregard for the safety of the public. 不论谁安置了炸弹都显示出对公众安全的全然漠视。

